ect category\n- The test_router_intent_lookup.py confirms this by checking that lowercase intent like "code" should be used to map to the correct execution plan\n\n\nBug Analysis:\n- In router.py\'s classify_intent() function, the intent is not being lowercased before lookup\n- Current code: `intent = classification.get("intent", "chat")`\n- This means uppercase intents like "CODE" are not matching INTENT_CATEGORIES keys\n- Test failure confirms that uppercase intent is not being normalized\n\n\n\nBug Fix Confirmation:\n- Modified router.py to normalize intent to lowercase\n- All 3 tests in test_router_intent_lookup.py passed successfully\n- Py_compile check passed\n- Changes limited to router.py as specified\n- Fixes uppercase intent matching issue\n\n\nRouter Intent Classification Analysis:\n\nKey Components:\n1. INTENT_CATEGORIES dictionary defines 6 intent categories:\n   - research\n   - code\n   - ops\n   - creative\n   - analysis\n   - chat\n\n2. classify_intent() function workflow:\n   - Uses OpenRouter API to classify query\n   - Handles JSON parsing from LLM response\n   - Matches intent to INTENT_CATEGORIES\n   - Assigns execution plan based on intent\n\n3. Potential Issue Location:\n   - Line with `intent = classification.get("intent", "chat").lower()`\n   - Ensures lowercase intent matching\n   - Prevents uppercase intent lookup failures\n\nValidation Required:\n- Confirm lowercase normalization works correctly\n- Verify all intent categories are accessible\n- Check fallback to "chat" intent works as expected\n\n\nRouter Intent Classification Bug Research:\n\nLocation: router.py\nBug: Intent classification fails with uppercase intent strings\nCurrent Behavior: \n- Intent lookup does not normalize case\n- Uppercase intents like "CODE" fall back to "chat" category\n- Prevents correct intent routing\n\nKey Findings:\n1. INTENT_CATEGORIES contains lowercase keys\n2. classify_intent() needs lowercase normalization\n3. Proposed fix: Add .lower() to intent retrieval\n\nVerification Steps:\n- Lowercase normalization added\n- All tests in test_router_intent_lookup.py passed\n- No changes to unrelated files\n- Py_compile check successful\n\nRecommended Fix:\nChange: `intent = classification.get("intent", "chat").lower()`\nPurpose: Normalize intent case before lookup\n\n\nRouter Intent Classification Bug Research:\n\nBug Location: router.py\nSpecific Issue: Intent classification fails with uppercase intent strings\n\nKey Findings:\n1. INTENT_CATEGORIES contains lowercase keys\n2. classify_intent() requires lowercase normalization\n3. Current implementation does not handle case-insensitive intent matching\n\nVerification Steps Completed:\n- Examined router.py contents\n- Ran tests in test_router_intent_lookup.py\n- Confirmed py_compile check passed\n- Validated lowercase normalization fix\n\nProposed Solution:\nModify intent retrieval to use .lower() method:\n`intent = classification.get("intent", "chat").lower()`\n\nThis ensures:\n- Uppercase intents are normalized\n- Correct intent routing\n- Fallback to "chat" works as expected\n\nTest Validation:\n- All 3 tests in test_router_intent_lookup.py passed\n- No changes to unrelated files\n- Py_compile check successful\n\nThe timeout value in `router.py` is being incorrectly halved (divided by 2 with `// 2`) when creating the execution plan. The `tests/test_router_timeout_bug.py` confirms this. The tests fail because the expected timeout does not match the actual timeout.\n\nBefore modification, the tests in `tests/test_router_timeout_bug.py` failed. Specifically, `test_code_intent_timeout_correct` failed with `AssertionError: Expected timeout 300, got 150`. The file `router.py` contains an intent classification router. The `classify_intent` function classifies user queries into intent categories and selects appropriate skill sets, models, and success criteria. The timeout for each intent is halved in line 201: `\'timeout\': plan[\'timeout\'] // 2,`. The test `tests/test_router_timeout_bug.py` tests that the timeout is set correctly based on the `INTENT_CATEGORIES` in `router.py`.\n</research notes>\n\n<environment inventory>\n**Operating System:** Linux (Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS 24.04)\n\n**Found CLI developer tools:** fd, rg, fzf, git (git version 2.43.0), g++ (g++ (Ubuntu 13.3.0-6ubuntu2~24.04.1) 13.3.0), gcc (gcc (Ubuntu 13.3.0-6ubuntu2~24.04.1) 13.3.0), make, pkg-config\n\n**Python Environments:**\n- Python 3.11.14 at `/home/exedev/.hermes/hermes-agent/venv/bin/python3.11`\n- Python 3.12.3 at `/home/exedev/autonomy/labs/agent-harness-bakeoff/.venv-raaid/bin/python3`\n- Python 3.12.3 at `/home/exedev/autonomy/labs/agent-harness-bakeoff/.venv-raaid/bin/python`\n- Python 3.12.3 at `/home/exedev/autonomy/labs/agent-harness-bakeoff/.venv-raaid/bin/python3.12`\n- venv (builtin): available\n- virtualenv: installed (version virtualenv 21.2.0 from /home/exedev/.local/lib/python3.12/site-packages/virtualenv/__init__.py)\n- uv: installed (version 0.10.4)\n- pipenv: not installed\n- poetry: not installed\n- conda: not installed\n- pyenv: not installed\n- pipx: installed (version 1.4.3)\n\n**Package Managers:**\n- apt: found (apt 2.8.3 (amd64))\n- apt-get: found (apt 2.8.3 (amd64))\n\n**Developer Libraries:**\n- zlib: installed (version 1.3), libs: `-lz`\n- ICU: installed (version 74.2), libs: `-licuuc -licudata`\n- Not found: APR, Allegro, Armadillo, Assimp, BLAS, BerkeleyDB, Blaze, Blitz++, Boost, BoostTest, Boost_Asio, Boost_Beast, Boost_uBLAS, BoringSSL, Botan, Box2D, Brotli, Bullet, CMake, CUDA, Caffe, Cairo, ChakraCore, Crypto++, DearImGui, DirectX, Duktape, Eigen, FFmpeg, FMOD, GLFW, GLM, GLib, GSL, GStreamer, GTK, GnuTLS, GoogleTest, Guile, HDF5, HIP, IntelMKL, Irrlicht, Jack, JavaScriptCore, JoltPhysics, LAPACK, LZ4, LevelDB, LibreSSL, LightGBM, Lua, LuaJIT, MPI, MQTT, MXNet, Magnum, MicrosoftMPI, Mono, MuJoCo, MySQL, NanoVG, Newton, ODE, OGRE, ONNX, OpenACC, OpenAL, OpenAL_Soft, OpenBLAS, OpenCL, OpenCV, OpenGL, OpenMP, OpenSSL, OpenVINO, Phys